com.mashery.trafficmanager.processor

Annotation Type ProcessorBean


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface ProcessorBean

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      String name
      The name of the processor as defined in the portal

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean enabled
      Indicates if the processor is enabled or disabled
      boolean immediate
      Indicates if the processor is enabled immediately upon deployment or lazy-initialized
      String lifeCycleClass
      Indicates the life-cycle class which should receive the call-backs when the processor is activated and in-activated If the processor implements the life-cycle interface then the life-cycle class need not be declared

    • Element Detail

      • name

        public abstract String name
        The name of the processor as defined in the portal
        Returns:
        the name of the processor that is used in the dashboard to identify the processor to which a call is made

      • enabled

        public abstract boolean enabled
        Indicates if the processor is enabled or disabled
        Returns:
        if the processor is enabled, defaults to true
        Default:
        true

      • immediate

        public abstract boolean immediate
        Indicates if the processor is enabled immediately upon deployment or lazy-initialized
        Returns:
        if the processor is enabled immediately, defaults to true
        Default:
        false

      • lifeCycleClass

        public abstract String lifeCycleClass
        Indicates the life-cycle class which should receive the call-backs when the processor is activated and in-activated If the processor implements the life-cycle interface then the life-cycle class need not be declared
        Returns:
        the lifecycle class which will receive callbacks when the processor is first invoked and when the processor is removed from the runtime
        Default:
        ""
